dataStructure.name: sid.org.tmforum.tip.resource.res.log.itf.LogicalInterface
dataStructure.description:
This is an abstract class that serves as the superclass for all virtual interfaces. LogicalInterfaces are also called virtual interfaces. This is because a LogicalInterface has no hardware associated with it, and it is not physically connected to a network. It serves as a convenient aggregation point for running different relationships that affect its subclasses, thereby avoiding having to instantiate multiple relationships that are essentially the same.

This entity is abstract

This entity is optional
